.TH SCREENCAST "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
screencast \- Record your desktop
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B screencast
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,OUTPUT_FILE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B screencast
is a script for recording your desktop screen. It provides a simple interface for screen capture with optional audio recording.
.PP
The script uses ffmpeg for encoding and supports various output formats.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B screencast
Start recording to default file
.TP
.B screencast ~/Videos/demo.mp4
Record to specific file
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/screencast/settings.conf
User configuration file for screencast preferences
.TP
.B ~/Videos/
Default output directory
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
Required command (ffmpeg) not found
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Uses ffmpeg for recording
.IP \(bu 2
Supports audio capture
.IP \(bu 2
Multiple output formats supported
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Required:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
ffmpeg - For video encoding
.IP \(bu 2
xdpyinfo or xrandr - For screen resolution detection
.RE
.TP
.B Optional:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
pulseaudio - For audio capture
.IP \(bu 2
slop - For region selection
.RE
